claims:
Claims 1. A method of managing communication between computing nodes, the method comprising: at a topology controller: receiving (414) a topology request at the topology controller; based at least partially on the topology request, selecting (416) an input-output (I/O) link connecting an input node to a destination node from a plurality of I/O links including at least: a direct I/O link (420) between the input node and the destination node, and a switched I/O link (418) between the input node and the destination node; and configuring (422) an active I/O link between the input node and the destination node based on the selected I/O link. 2. The method of claim 1. wherein configuring the active I/O link includes actuating a cross- point switch. 3. The method of claim 1 or 2, wherein the topology request is received from the input node. 4. The method of any preceding claim, wherein the direct I/O link directly connects a first topology switch of the input node to a second topology switch of the destination node. 5. The method of any preceding claim, wherein the switched I/O link connects a first topology switch of the input node to a network switch and connects the network switch to a second topology 7 switch of the destination node. 6. The method of any preceding claim, wherein selecting a direct link between the input node and the destination node includes configuring a plurality 7 of direct links between the input node and the destination node based at least partially on the topology request. 7. The method of any preceding claim, wherein configuring the active I/O link includes changing a physical connection between a first connector of the input node to a second connector of the destination node. 8. The method of any preceding claim, wherein selecting a direct link includes selecting a fixed link topology 7 . 9. The method of claim 8, wherein the fixed link topology 7 is selected from a group including ring, tree, star, and hierarchical. 10. The method of claim 8. wherein the fixed link topology 7 includes at least one network switch. 11. The method of any preceding claim, further comprising, after configuring the active I/O link to a direct I/O link, powering down a network switch of the switched I/O link. 12. A system for managing a topology of a distributed computing system, the system 

 comprising: an input node (502); a destination node (504-1); a first topology switch (526-1) associated with the input node and in data communication with the input node; a second topology switch (526-2) associated with the destination node and in data communication with the destination node; and a topology controller (528) configured to actuate at least the first topology switch to selectively direct information from the input node to one of: a direct I/O link (508) between the first topology controller and the second topology controller, and a switched I/O link (510) between the first topology controller and the second topology controller. 13. The system of claim 12, wherein the topology controller is in data communication with an allocator. 14. The system of claim 12, wherein the topology 7 controller is part of an allocator. 15. The system of any of claims 12-14, wherein the topology controller is configured to actuate at least the first topology 7 switch to selectively direct information based at least partially on a topology 7 request received at the topology controller. 16. The system of any of claims 12-15, wherein at least one of the first topology' switch and the second topology 7 switch is a cross-point switch. 17. The system of any of claims 12-16, wherein the switched I/O link includes a network switch. 18. The system of claim 17, wherein the network sw'itch has a latency greater than 200 nanoseconds. 19. A method of managing communication between computing nodes, the method comprising: receiving a computational process request at a machine learning model (632); determining at least part of a topology request w ith the machine learning model; and at a topology 7 controller (528): receiving (414) the topology request at the topology controller; based at least partially on the computational process request, selecting (416) an input-output (I/O) link connecting an input node to a destination node from a plurality' of I/O links including at least: a direct I/O link (420) between the input node and the destination node, and a switched I/O link (418) between the input node and the destination node; 

 and configuring (422) an active I/O link between the input node and the destination node based on the selected I/O link. 20. The method of claim 19, wherein the machine learning model is further in communication with an allocator.
